==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thug
<hw>Thug</hw> <pr>(th⟦ucr⟧g; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>thag</ets> a deceiver, robber.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of an
association of robbers and murderers in India who practiced murder by
stealthy approaches, and from religious motives. They have been nearly
exterminated by the British government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An assassin; a ruffian; a rough.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Thugs</xex> and midnight rounders.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>The
Century.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thuggee</ent>⟦br⟧
